HWLldpPortId.description: This TC describes the format of a port identifier string. Objects of this type are always used with an associated LldpPortIdSubtype object, which identifies the format of the particular LldpPortId object instance. If the associated LldpPortIdSubtype object has a value of 'interfaceAlias(1)', then the octet string identifies a particular instance of the ifAlias object (defined in IETF RFC 2863). If the particular ifAlias object does not contain any values, another port identifier type should be used. If the associated LldpPortIdSubtype object has a value of 'portComponent(2)', then the octet string identifies a particular instance of the entPhysicalAlias object (defined in IETF RFC 2737) for a port or backplane component. If the associated LldpPortIdSubtype object has a value of 'macAddress(3)', then this string identifies a particular unicast source address (encoded in network byte order and IEEE 802.3 canonical bit order) associated with the port (IEEE Std 802-2001). If the associated LldpPortIdSubtype object has a value of 'networkAddress(4)', then this string identifies a network address associated with the port. The first octet contains the IANA AddressFamilyNumbers enumeration value for the specific address type, and octets 2 through N contain the networkAddress address value in network byte order. If the associated LldpPortIdSubtype object has a value of 'interfaceName(5)', then the octet string identifies a particular instance of the ifName object (defined in IETF RFC 2863). If the particular ifName object does not contain any values, another port identifier type should be used. If the associated LldpPortIdSubtype object has a value of 'agentCircuitId(6)', then this string identifies a agent-local identifier of the circuit (defined in RFC 3046). If the associated LldpPortIdSubtype object has a value of 'local(7)', then this string identifies a locally assigned port ID.
HWLldpPortId.name: HWLldpPortId

nqaPathMtuStatsDrops.description: The times probes of the test dropped due to sending or connecting failure.
nqaPathMtuStatsDrops.name: nqaPathMtuStatsDrops

nqaPathMtuStatsEntry.description: Defines an entry in the nqaPathMtuStatsTable.
nqaPathMtuStatsEntry.name: nqaPathMtuStatsEntry

nqaPathMtuStatsIndex.description: The index of path MTU statistics table, and the times of dispatching dependency tests.
nqaPathMtuStatsIndex.name: nqaPathMtuStatsIndex

nqaPathMtuStatsOptimumFirstStep.description: The optimum first step of the path MTU test. It will take effect if the specified step is lower than it.
nqaPathMtuStatsOptimumFirstStep.name: nqaPathMtuStatsOptimumFirstStep

nqaPathMtuStatsPathMtu.description: The value of current path MTU.
nqaPathMtuStatsPathMtu.name: nqaPathMtuStatsPathMtu

nqaPathMtuStatsProbeResponses.description: The number of received reponse packets.
nqaPathMtuStatsProbeResponses.name: nqaPathMtuStatsProbeResponses

nqaPathMtuStatsTable.description: The statistics collection database. Defines the path MTU Operations Statistics Table for storing the statistics of a path MTU test.
nqaPathMtuStatsTable.name: nqaPathMtuStatsTable

nqaPathMtuStatsTimeouts.description: The number of occasions when a NQA operation was not completed before a timeout occurred, i.e. nqaAdminCtrlTimeOut was exceeded.
nqaPathMtuStatsTimeouts.name: nqaPathMtuStatsTimeouts

nqaPppoeAuthorizationTimeout.description: The time for authentication of PPPoE operation.
nqaPppoeAuthorizationTimeout.name: nqaPppoeAuthorizationTimeout

nqaPppoeClientIpAddress.description: The client ip address of PPPoE operation.
nqaPppoeClientIpAddress.name: nqaPppoeClientIpAddress

nqaPppoeClientSessionId.description: The client sessionID of PPPoE operation.
nqaPppoeClientSessionId.name: nqaPppoeClientSessionId

nqaPppoeConnectionTime.description: The time for connection of PPPoE operation.
nqaPppoeConnectionTime.name: nqaPppoeConnectionTime

nqaPppoeDiscoveryTimeout.description: The time for discovery of PPPoE operation.
nqaPppoeDiscoveryTimeout.name: nqaPppoeDiscoveryTimeout

nqaPppoeGatewayIpAddress.description: The gateway ip address of PPPoE operation.
nqaPppoeGatewayIpAddress.name: nqaPppoeGatewayIpAddress

nqaPppoeLcpTimeout.description: The time for lcp negotiate of PPPoE operation.
nqaPppoeLcpTimeout.name: nqaPppoeLcpTimeout

nqaPppoeNcpTimeout.description: The time for ncp negotiate of PPPoE operation.
nqaPppoeNcpTimeout.name: nqaPppoeNcpTimeout

nqaPppoeRedialIndex.description: The index of PPPoE statistics table, and the redialing times of dispatching dependency tests.
nqaPppoeRedialIndex.name: nqaPppoeRedialIndex

nqaPppoeStatsCurrentPhase.description: The current phase of PPPoE operation.
nqaPppoeStatsCurrentPhase.name: nqaPppoeStatsCurrentPhase

nqaPppoeStatsEntry.description: A table which contains the rolling accumulated history of the PPPoE operation. This entry is created only if the nqaAdminCtrlType is pppoe.
nqaPppoeStatsEntry.name: nqaPppoeStatsEntry

nqaPppoeStatsErrorMessage.description: The error message result of PPPoE operation.
nqaPppoeStatsErrorMessage.name: nqaPppoeStatsErrorMessage

nqaPppoeStatsIndex.description: The index of PPPoE statistics table, and the executing times of dispatching dependency tests.
nqaPppoeStatsIndex.name: nqaPppoeStatsIndex

nqaPppoeStatsTable.description: A table which contains the rolling accumulated history of the PPPoE operation.
nqaPppoeStatsTable.name: nqaPppoeStatsTable

nqaPppoeStatsTestCompleted.description: Generated at the completion of a PPPoE test when the corresponding nqaAdminParaTrapGeneration object is set to testCompletion(2). (Only for PPPoE)
nqaPppoeStatsTestCompleted.name: nqaPppoeStatsTestCompleted

nqaPppoeStatsTestFailed.description: Generated when a PPPoE test is determined to have failed when the corresponding nqaAdminParaTrapGeneration object is set to testFailure(1). (Only for PPPoE))
nqaPppoeStatsTestFailed.name: nqaPppoeStatsTestFailed

nqaReset.description: Clears all the enabled test configurations. (The value range: enable:1; disable:2. The default value is disable(2))
nqaReset.name: nqaReset

nqaResultsAddress.description: The destination address (TraceRoute is the destination address of each hop, and ping is the destination address of tests).
nqaResultsAddress.name: nqaResultsAddress

nqaResultsAddressType.description: The destination address type, and the value range can be unknown(0), ipv4(1) and dns(16).
nqaResultsAddressType.name: nqaResultsAddressType

nqaResultsBusies.description: The times of failure to apply resource due to the busy system. such as apply memory or create socket failure.
nqaResultsBusies.name: nqaResultsBusies

nqaResultsCompletionTimeMax.description: The maximum RTT (for Traceroute and LSP Traceroute, it is the maximum RTT among all the packets of next hop) of all packets in executing a test.
nqaResultsCompletionTimeMax.name: nqaResultsCompletionTimeMax

nqaResultsCompletionTimeMin.description: The minimum RTT (for Traceroute and LSP Traceroute, it is the minimum RTT among all the packet of next hop) of all packets for executing a test.
nqaResultsCompletionTimeMin.name: nqaResultsCompletionTimeMin

nqaResultsCurHopCount.description: It is equal to the hop count index executed by current Traceroute or LSP Traceroute tests. Ping/LSP Ping does not use this entry. The default value is 0.
nqaResultsCurHopCount.name: nqaResultsCurHopCount

nqaResultsCurProbeCount.description: The total count of probe packets of Traceroute or LSP Traceroute test in a hop count index.
nqaResultsCurProbeCount.name: nqaResultsCurProbeCount

nqaResultsDisconnects.description: The times of consecutive failures. For connectionless protocol type of test,this number should be zero.
nqaResultsDisconnects.name: nqaResultsDisconnects

nqaResultsDrops.description: The times probes of the test dropped due to sending or connecting failure.
nqaResultsDrops.name: nqaResultsDrops

nqaResultsEntry.description: The operation of this table is same as that of nqaResultsTable.
nqaResultsEntry.name: nqaResultsEntry

nqaResultsHopIndex.description: The hop index. If the test type is Traceroute or LSP Traceroute, the entry only defines one hop. For other types, the default value is 1.
nqaResultsHopIndex.name: nqaResultsHopIndex

nqaResultsIndex.description: The result table index and times of dispatching dependency tests. Each test can only reserve 5 records. The result table only contains icmp/dns/dlsw/lspPing/Traceroute/LSP Traceroute/tcp/udp/snmp/dhcp Traceroute information.
nqaResultsIndex.name: nqaResultsIndex

nqaResultsLastGoodPath.description: The date and time when the last complete path was determined.
nqaResultsLastGoodPath.name: nqaResultsLastGoodPath

nqaResultsLastGoodProbe.description: Date and time when the last response was received for a probe.
nqaResultsLastGoodProbe.name: nqaResultsLastGoodProbe

nqaResultsLostPacketRatio.description: The ratio of the packets lost to all packets sent in the test.
nqaResultsLostPacketRatio.name: nqaResultsLostPacketRatio

nqaResultsNoConnections.description: The number of occasions when a NQA operation could not be initiated because the connection to the target has not been established. For all other nqaAdminCtrlType this object will remain zero. This cannot occur for connectionless protocols, but may occur for connection oriented protocols, such as TCP. Since a NQA operation was never initiated, the completion time of these operations are not accumulated, nor do they increment nqaResultsCompletions.
nqaResultsNoConnections.name: nqaResultsNoConnections

nqaResultsProbeFailed.description: Generated when a probe failure is detected when the corresponding nqaAdminParaTrapGeneration object is set to probeFailure(0) subject to the value of nqaAdminParaTrapProbeFailureFilter. The object nqaAdminParaTrapProbeFailureFilter can be used to specify the number of successive probe failures that are required before this notification can be generated.(except for HTTP or Jitter or FTP)
nqaResultsProbeFailed.name: nqaResultsProbeFailed

nqaResultsProbeResponses.description: Number of responses received for the corresponding test. The value of this object MUST be reported as 0 when no probe responses have been received.
nqaResultsProbeResponses.name: nqaResultsProbeResponses

nqaResultsRTDOverThresholds.description: The times of successful statistics test RTD (Round Trip Delay) over the threshold.
nqaResultsRTDOverThresholds.name: nqaResultsRTDOverThresholds

nqaResultsRttAvg.description: The average of RTTs that were successfully measured by tests.
nqaResultsRttAvg.name: nqaResultsRttAvg

nqaResultsSentProbes.description: The value of this object reflects the number of probes sent for the corresponding test. The value of this object MUST be reported as 0 when no probes have been sent.
nqaResultsSentProbes.name: nqaResultsSentProbes

nqaResultsSequenceErrors.description: The number of NQA operation completions received with an unexpected sequence identifier. For all other values of nqaAdminCtrlType this object will remain zero. When this has occurred some of the possible reasons maybe: - a duplicate packet was received - a response was received after it had timed-out - a corrupted packet was received and was not detected
nqaResultsSequenceErrors.name: nqaResultsSequenceErrors

nqaResultsSumCompletionTime.description: The sum of RTT (response time) of all packets of each hop for executing Traceroute, LSP Traceroute tests. The sum of RTT (response time) of sent packets for executing ping, lsp ping and disman-ping tests and so on.
nqaResultsSumCompletionTime.name: nqaResultsSumCompletionTime

nqaResultsSumCompletionTime2High.description: The high order 32 bits of the accumulated squares of completion times (in milliseconds) of NQA operations which complete successfully. See the nqaResultsSumCompletionTime2Low object for a definition of Low/High Order.
nqaResultsSumCompletionTime2High.name: nqaResultsSumCompletionTime2High

nqaResultsSumCompletionTime2Low.description: The low order 32 bits of the accumulated squares of completion times (in milliseconds) of NQA operations which complete successfully. Low/High order is defined where the binary number will look as follows: ------------------------------------------------- | High order 32 bits | Low order 32 bits | ------------------------------------------------- For example the number 4294967296 would have all Low order bits as '0' and the rightmost High order bit will be 1 (zeros,1).
nqaResultsSumCompletionTime2Low.name: nqaResultsSumCompletionTime2Low

nqaResultsTable.description: Defines the test Results Extend Table for providing the capability of performing test operations at a remote host. The results of these operations are stored in the nqaResultsTable . The operation of this table is same as that of nqaResultsTable.
nqaResultsTable.name: nqaResultsTable

nqaResultsTestAttempts.description: The times of executing tests, which includes the times of successful execution, failed execution and interruption (interrupted by human or system). The current number of test attempts. The value of this object MUST be started at 0.
nqaResultsTestAttempts.name: nqaResultsTestAttempts

nqaResultsTestCompleted.description: Generated at the completion of a nqa test when the corresponding nqaAdminParaTrapGeneration object is set to testCompletion(2).(except for HTTP or Jitter or FTP)
nqaResultsTestCompleted.name: nqaResultsTestCompleted

nqaResultsTestFailed.description: Generated when a nqa test is determined to have failed when the corresponding nqaAdminParaTrapGeneration object is set to testFailure(1). In this instance nqaAdminParaTrapTestFailureFilter should specify the number of probes in a test required to have failed in order to consider the test as failed. (Except for HTTP or Jitter or FTP)
nqaResultsTestFailed.name: nqaResultsTestFailed

nqaResultsThresholdNotification.description: If the time of executing tests exceeds the nqaAdminCtrlThreshold1, the system sends trap information.(except for HTTP or Jitter or FTP)
nqaResultsThresholdNotification.name: nqaResultsThresholdNotification

nqaResultsTimeouts.description: The number of occasions when a NQA operation was not completed before a timeout occurred, i.e. nqaAdminCtrlTimeOut was exceeded.
nqaResultsTimeouts.name: nqaResultsTimeouts

nqaRisingAlarmNotification.description: Sending trap messages when the value of the monitored object exceeds nqaAlarmUpperThreshold.
nqaRisingAlarmNotification.name: nqaRisingAlarmNotification

nqaScheduleAgeTime.description: Specifies the aging time of the test instance, the time how long the test instance will be reserved in NQA, after the test instance is inactive. Setting the value to 0 indicates reserving the test instance eternally.
nqaScheduleAgeTime.name: nqaScheduleAgeTime

nqaScheduleElapsedTime.description: The elapsed time (the period of time after task dispatch).
nqaScheduleElapsedTime.name: nqaScheduleElapsedTime

nqaScheduleEndTime.description: Specifies the end time of the test instance.
nqaScheduleEndTime.name: nqaScheduleEndTime

nqaScheduleEndType.description: Specifies the end type of the test instance. The object is used together with nqaScheduleEndTime.
nqaScheduleEndType.name: nqaScheduleEndType

nqaScheduleLastCollectIndex.description: Specifies the index of the latest collection statistics result record in the collection result table.
nqaScheduleLastCollectIndex.name: nqaScheduleLastCollectIndex

nqaScheduleLastFinishIndex.description: Specifies the latest finished test of the test instance, which is used as the index of the result table.
nqaScheduleLastFinishIndex.name: nqaScheduleLastFinishIndex

nqaScheduleNumOfInitiations.description: Specifies the times that the test instance has been initialed. This object is used as the index of the result table, HTTP statistics table, jitter statistics table, FTP statistics table and history table.
nqaScheduleNumOfInitiations.name: nqaScheduleNumOfInitiations

nqaScheduleOperStatus.description: Specifies the status of dispatching operation: - reset: Clear all the records of the test instance. - stop: Stop the test instance, if it's running. - restart: Stop the test instance, if it's running, and restart the test instance immediately. - active: The test instance is running; the parameters of the test instances can't be changed. - inactive: The test instance doesn't be scheduled; the parameters of the test instances can be changed.
nqaScheduleOperStatus.name: nqaScheduleOperStatus

nqaScheduleStartTime.description: Specifies the start time of the test instance. Setting the value to 0 indicates to start the test instance immediately. After configuring this object, the status of the test instance is active, and the parameters of the test instance can't be changed.
nqaScheduleStartTime.name: nqaScheduleStartTime

nqaScheduleStartType.description: Specifies the start type of the test instance. The object is used together with nqaScheduleStartTime.
nqaScheduleStartType.name: nqaScheduleStartType

nqaServerEnable.description: Enables NQA server, which can be the echo server of TCP, UDP and jitter type test instance.
nqaServerEnable.name: nqaServerEnable

nqaSupportServerType.description: Test type that the current device supports. Data structure of the type is in the format of bits. Each bit represents a test type. tcpServer(0), udpServer(1), icmpServer(2) The value #0x00 indicates don't suppourt all servertypes.
nqaSupportServerType.name: nqaSupportServerType

nqaSupportTestType.description: Test type that the current device supports. Data structure of the type is in the format of bits. Each bit represents a test type. The mappings between bits and tests are as follows: icmp(0), tcp(1), udp(2), http(3), ftp(4), jitter(5), snmp(6), trace(7), lspPing(8), lspTrace(9), dns(10), dhcp(11), dlsw(12), pwe3Ping(13), pwe3Trace(14), mPing(15), mTrace(16), macPing(17), macTunnelPing(18), lspJitter(19), icmpJitter(20), pathJitter(21), pathMtu(22), pppoe(23), vplsmPing(24), vplsmacPing(25), vplsmacTrace(26), vplsMTrace(27), gmacping(28), gmactrace(29), mactrace(30), vplspwping(31), vplspwtrace(32) The value #0x00 indicates don't suppourt all testtypes.
nqaSupportTestType.name: nqaSupportTestType

nqaTcpServerAddress.description: Specifies the address of TCP server.
nqaTcpServerAddress.name: nqaTcpServerAddress

nqaTcpServerAddressType.description: Specifies the address type of TCP server.
nqaTcpServerAddressType.name: nqaTcpServerAddressType

nqaTcpServerEntry.description: A table which contains the status of nqa tcp server configuration information. This entry is included not only the tcp server ip address but also the tcp server tcp port. If used for VPN it is also included the VPN name.
nqaTcpServerEntry.name: nqaTcpServerEntry

nqaTcpServerPort.description: Specifies the port number on which TCP server is listening.
nqaTcpServerPort.name: nqaTcpServerPort

nqaTcpServerStatus.description: Specifies the operation of the TCP server, creating or deleting.
nqaTcpServerStatus.name: nqaTcpServerStatus
nqaTcpServerStatus.reference: See definition of RowStatus in RFC 2579, 'Textual Conventions for SMIv2.'

nqaTcpServerTable.description: A table which contains the status of nqa tcp server configuration information.
nqaTcpServerTable.name: nqaTcpServerTable

nqaTcpServerVrfName.description: Specifies the VRF (VPN Routing & Forwarding) instances name of the TCP server.
nqaTcpServerVrfName.name: nqaTcpServerVrfName

nqaTimeOfLastSetError.description: The time of the last configuration error. (0 indicates that the configuration does not fail).
nqaTimeOfLastSetError.name: nqaTimeOfLastSetError

nqaUdpServerAddress.description: Specifies the address of UDP server.
nqaUdpServerAddress.name: nqaUdpServerAddress

nqaUdpServerAddressType.description: Specifies the address type of UDP server.
nqaUdpServerAddressType.name: nqaUdpServerAddressType

nqaUdpServerEntry.description: A table which contains the status of nqa udp server configuration information. This entry is includeed not only the udp server ip address but also the udp server udp port.If used for VPN it is also included the VPN name.
nqaUdpServerEntry.name: nqaUdpServerEntry

nqaUdpServerPort.description: Specifies the port number on which UDP server is listening.
nqaUdpServerPort.name: nqaUdpServerPort

nqaUdpServerStatus.description: Specifies the operation of the UDP server, creating or deleting.
nqaUdpServerStatus.name: nqaUdpServerStatus
nqaUdpServerStatus.reference: See definition of RowStatus in RFC 2579, 'Textual Conventions for SMIv2.'

nqaUdpServerTable.description: A table which contains the status of nqa udp server configuration information.
nqaUdpServerTable.name: nqaUdpServerTable

nqaUdpServerVrfName.description: Specifies the VRF (VPN Routing & Forwarding) instances name of the UDP server.
nqaUdpServerVrfName.name: nqaUdpServerVrfName

nqaVersion.description: The NQA version (for example, 1.1). It can be used for version management.
nqaVersion.name: nqaVersion

nqaVplsMTraceHistoryCACExist.description: Whether the connection admission control comfiguration of current VSI is exist.
nqaVplsMTraceHistoryCACExist.name: nqaVplsMTraceHistoryCACExist

nqaVplsMTraceHistoryCompletionTime.description: The amount of time measured in milliseconds from when a probe was sent to when its response was received or when it timed out. The value of this object is reported as 0 when it is not possible to transmit a probe.
nqaVplsMTraceHistoryCompletionTime.name: nqaVplsMTraceHistoryCompletionTime

nqaVplsMTraceHistoryEntry.description: Defines a table for storing the results of a test operation. Entries in this table are limited by the value of the corresponding nqaAdminParaHistoryRowMax.
nqaVplsMTraceHistoryEntry.name: nqaVplsMTraceHistoryEntry

nqaVplsMTraceHistoryFinishState.description: The finish state of a probe.
nqaVplsMTraceHistoryFinishState.name: nqaVplsMTraceHistoryFinishState

nqaVplsMTraceHistoryHitFlag.description: Whether the fib is hit on the device which received the packet.
nqaVplsMTraceHistoryHitFlag.name: nqaVplsMTraceHistoryHitFlag

nqaVplsMTraceHistoryHopIndex.description: The index of vpls multicast trace hop.
nqaVplsMTraceHistoryHopIndex.name: nqaVplsMTraceHistoryHopIndex

nqaVplsMTraceHistoryIGMPRouterPortLearni.description: The IGMP router port learning enable switch.
nqaVplsMTraceHistoryIGMPRouterPortLearni.name: nqaVplsMTraceHistoryIGMPRouterPortLearningEnable

nqaVplsMTraceHistoryIndex.description: The vpls multicast trace history table index and times for dispatching dependency tests.
nqaVplsMTraceHistoryIndex.name: nqaVplsMTraceHistoryIndex

nqaVplsMTraceHistoryLastRC.description: The last implementation method specific reply code received.
nqaVplsMTraceHistoryLastRC.name: nqaVplsMTraceHistoryLastRC

nqaVplsMTraceHistoryLastRSC.description: The last implementation method specific reply sub code received.
nqaVplsMTraceHistoryLastRSC.name: nqaVplsMTraceHistoryLastRSC

nqaVplsMTraceHistoryPWExist.description: Whether the forward PW is exist.
nqaVplsMTraceHistoryPWExist.name: nqaVplsMTraceHistoryPWExist

nqaVplsMTraceHistoryRcvLeaveCount.description: The received leave packet number for current IGMP version of current VSI.
nqaVplsMTraceHistoryRcvLeaveCount.name: nqaVplsMTraceHistoryRcvLeaveCount

nqaVplsMTraceHistoryRcvQueryCount.description: The received query packet number for current IGMP version of current VSI.
nqaVplsMTraceHistoryRcvQueryCount.name: nqaVplsMTraceHistoryRcvQueryCount

nqaVplsMTraceHistoryRcvReportCount.description: The received report packet number for current IGMP version of current VSI.
nqaVplsMTraceHistoryRcvReportCount.name: nqaVplsMTraceHistoryRcvReportCount

nqaVplsMTraceHistoryReceivedTtl.description: The value of ttl in the received packet.
nqaVplsMTraceHistoryReceivedTtl.name: nqaVplsMTraceHistoryReceivedTtl

nqaVplsMTraceHistoryRequireRouterAlertEn.description: The route alert requirement enable switch.
nqaVplsMTraceHistoryRequireRouterAlertEn.name: nqaVplsMTraceHistoryRequireRouterAlertEnable

nqaVplsMTraceHistoryResponseIndex.description: The index of vpls multicast trace responser.
nqaVplsMTraceHistoryResponseIndex.name: nqaVplsMTraceHistoryResponseIndex

nqaVplsMTraceHistoryResponserAddressType.description: The type of history record's Responser address.
nqaVplsMTraceHistoryResponserAddressType.name: nqaVplsMTraceHistoryResponserAddressType

nqaVplsMTraceHistorySuccessPathNode.description: Whether the response router is on the path of a probe. The default value is notonPath(2).
nqaVplsMTraceHistorySuccessPathNode.name: nqaVplsMTraceHistorySuccessPathNode

nqaVplsMTraceHistoryTable.description: Defines the remote vpls multicast trace operations test history table for storing the results of a test operation.
nqaVplsMTraceHistoryTable.name: nqaVplsMTraceHistoryTable

nqaVplsMTraceHistoryTimeStamp.description: The start time stamp of a probe.
nqaVplsMTraceHistoryTimeStamp.name: nqaVplsMTraceHistoryTimeStamp

nqaVplsMTraceHistoryUpStreamAddress.description: The last hop address of tests.
nqaVplsMTraceHistoryUpStreamAddress.name: nqaVplsMTraceHistoryUpStreamAddress

nqaVplsMTraceHistoryUpStreamAddressType.description: The type of history records' last hop address.
nqaVplsMTraceHistoryUpStreamAddressType.name: nqaVplsMTraceHistoryUpStreamAddressType

nqaVplsMacTracertHistoryAddress.description: The destination address of tests. For Traceroute, it is the destination address of each hop.
nqaVplsMacTracertHistoryAddress.name: nqaVplsMacTracertHistoryAddress

nqaVplsMacTracertHistoryAddressType.description: The address type of history records.
nqaVplsMacTracertHistoryAddressType.name: nqaVplsMacTracertHistoryAddressType

nqaVplsMacTracertHistoryCompletionTime.description: The completion time of a probe in milliseconds. The amount of time measured in milliseconds from when a probe was sent to when its response was received or when it timed out. The value of this object is reported as 0 when it is not possible to transmit a probe.
nqaVplsMacTracertHistoryCompletionTime.name: nqaVplsMacTracertHistoryCompletionTime

nqaVplsMacTracertHistoryDSEntry.description: Defines a table for storing the results of a test operation. Entries in this table are limited by the value of the corresponding nqaAdminParaHistoryRowMax.
nqaVplsMacTracertHistoryDSEntry.name: nqaVplsMacTracertHistoryDSEntry

nqaVplsMacTracertHistoryDSIndex.description: The VPLS mac trace history DS table index.
nqaVplsMacTracertHistoryDSIndex.name: nqaVplsMacTracertHistoryDSIndex

nqaVplsMacTracertHistoryDSTable.description: Defines the VPLS mac trace Operations test History Downstreanm Table for storing the results of a test operation.
nqaVplsMacTracertHistoryDSTable.name: nqaVplsMacTracertHistoryDSTable

nqaVplsMacTracertHistoryEntry.description: Defines a table for storing the results of a test operation. Entries in this table are limited by the value of the corresponding nqaAdminParaHistoryRowMax.
nqaVplsMacTracertHistoryEntry.name: nqaVplsMacTracertHistoryEntry

nqaVplsMacTracertHistoryFinishState.description: The finish state of a probe.
nqaVplsMacTracertHistoryFinishState.name: nqaVplsMacTracertHistoryFinishState

nqaVplsMacTracertHistoryHopIndex.description: The index of VPLS mac trace hop.
nqaVplsMacTracertHistoryHopIndex.name: nqaVplsMacTracertHistoryHopIndex

nqaVplsMacTracertHistoryIndex.description: The VPLS mac trace history table index and times for dispatching dependency tests.
nqaVplsMacTracertHistoryIndex.name: nqaVplsMacTracertHistoryIndex

nqaVplsMacTracertHistoryResponseIndex.description: The index of VPLS mac trace reply packet per hop.
nqaVplsMacTracertHistoryResponseIndex.name: nqaVplsMacTracertHistoryResponseIndex

nqaVplsMacTracertHistorySuccessPathNode.description: This object indicates whether it is a node along the path that passes the Trace test. By default, the value is false, indicating that the object is not a node along the path that passes the Trace test.
nqaVplsMacTracertHistorySuccessPathNode.name: nqaVplsMacTracertHistorySuccessPathNode

nqaVplsMacTracertHistoryTable.description: Defines the VPLS mac trace Operations test History Table for storing the results of a test operation.
nqaVplsMacTracertHistoryTable.name: nqaVplsMacTracertHistoryTable

nqaVplsMacTracertHistoryTimeStamp.description: The start time stamp of a probe.
nqaVplsMacTracertHistoryTimeStamp.name: nqaVplsMacTracertHistoryTimeStamp
